Neil H. Bowie v. The State. No. 23143. Delivered June 6, 1945. Appellant’s Motion for Rehearing Overruled (Without Written Opinion) June 28, 1945.

*511The opinion states the case.

Robert S. Durno, of Houston, for appellant. Ernest S. Goens, State’s Attorney, of Austin, for the State. HAWKINS, Presiding Judge.

Conviction is for embezzlement, punishment two years in the penitentiary.

The judgment is affirmed for the same reasons set forth in our opinion in No. 23,142.
